parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Steering Rack and Pinion Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering rack and pinion can cause sudden loss of power steering control, making it difficult to steer, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Leaking power steering fluid
wobbling or shaking of the steering wheel
difficulty steering
sudden loss of power steering control
and noise from the power steering pump.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering pump can cause sudden loss of power steering control, making it difficult to steer, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Leaking power steering fluid
noise from the power steering pump
and difficulty steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front strut mount can cause uneven tire wear, noise, and vibration, which can lead to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: Noise from the front of the vehicle
uneven tire wear
and vibration while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Failure of Rear Suspension Crossmember and Lateral Arm
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension crossmember and lateral arm can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Loud noises from the rear of the vehicle
rattling or thumping sounds when hitting bumps
and abnormal swaying or swerving of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Front Struts and Control Arms
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front struts and control arms can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, as well as premature wear on tires.
symptoms: Clicking or rattling noises from the front suspension
bouncing or rattling of the front wheels
loose or unstable feeling of the front tires
and excessive wear on tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit sudden loss of speed
hesitation
or complete failure to move
accompanied by unusual noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition Switch and Gear Selector Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch and gear selector can cause the vehicle to roll away, leading to accidents or property damage.
symptoms: The key can be removed from the ignition switch while the vehicle is in gear
and the vehicle may roll away without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the traction control system can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or difficulty merging into traffic.
symptoms: The traction control system may engage too quickly or stay engaged too long
reducing power available to the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cruise Control and Trip Gauge Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the cruise control and trip gauge can cause inconvenience and distraction to the driver.
symptoms: The cruise control may malfunction
and the trip gauge may fail to display accurate information.
